caption: I love Potbelly Sandwich Shop! Literally has the best spicy chicken sandwich. It's juicy and jam packed with flavor. The curly fries are amazing as well and held up through delivery!
I can say this place does it for me. The service was helpful and kind. The place has a cool feel to it. Menu is like a place in Miami I enjoyed
I love this place. Looking forward to returning with my coworkers. Prices are fair I would say.

I'm going to dream about this sandwich for days.. the Spanish Godfather had tons of flavor and texture omg the cheese... dios mio. Also added avocado and they were pretty generous with the portion which I love. The bread was also to die for- perfectly toasted. I had a side order of bay chips which I believe they make themselves in the shop! It was a little too salty for my taste, but want to try the pepper flavor next time.

Pot belly sandwich shop has a good selection of sandwiches and voodoo chips.  The shop works like a well oiled machine and dont worry as even a line stretching out of the door only has a wait time of 5 to 10 minutes. They have plenty of options from the classic ham and cheese sandwich with mayo to a spicy Cuban sub with mustard and no pickles just the way you like it.... I mean.... It's a chain so. If you've been to a potbelly shop before expect the same

Sandwiches are ok but prices are increasing while other nearby delis are not. Since the sandwiches here are relatively small, you kind of got what you paid for previously. Now that the prices are nearing the price of other sandwich shops (for a smaller sandwich), it may not be worth it anymore in the near future. What is truely unique about this shop is their peppers and pickles. But if they are eventually going to charge you $10 for a 6 inch sandwich, then it just isnt worth it. Lots of seating in here but expect to come out with a particular odor.
